create a folder and create a sub folder called client where you will install react.
npx create-react-app . within the client folder

create a file called server.js and install nodemon and reference nodemon in package.json with server
replacing index all in package.json

install the folloing packages

express
mongoose
nodemon as a dev dependency.

in the client remove the git by running
rm -rf .git

to check if it is gone we use the command
ls -a

create a .gitignore in the root directory

Then edit the package.json file in root directory by adding the following

/node_modules
node_modules/

config.env

finally add git by running the command below in the root folder

git init

After running the command above it should gray out these file and folders. Meaning they will not be added to the 
github repository.





